As founder of Andrews Distributing, Barry Andrews has been instrumental in his company’s advancement and growth in the Texas beer business. With over 32 years of experience in this exciting industry, Barry has grown Andrews to a company of 1,000 employees…



Barry AndrewsChairman/CEO

As founder of Andrews Distributing, Barry Andrews has been instrumental in his company’s advancement and growth in the Texas beer business. With over 32 years of experience in this exciting industry, Barry has grown Andrews to a company of 1,000 employees and 12 warehouses in North and South Texas. 
Barry is a graduate of Southwest Texas State University and after college he returned to his hometown, Corpus Christi, where he founded Andrews Distributing in 1976. Barry is an active civic leader in both Corpus Christi and Dallas, and has served in numerous capacities through various industry organizations. Barry also enjoys being politically active to help support the advancement of the beer industry in Texas and nationwide.  He and his wife have two children and two granddaughters.






President
Mike McGuire Read More >>
As president of Andrews Distributing, Mike serves the team by communicating its purpose, vision and values and is responsible for working with the organization on delivering service excellence for their customers. Andrews’ purpose is brand building...



Mike McGuirePresident

As president of Andrews Distributing, Mike serves the team by communicating its purpose, vision and values and is responsible for working with the organization on delivering service excellence for their customers. Andrews’ purpose is brand building, in the greater service of thriving team members and stakeholders. The team lives by the core values set out in the company’s value wheel. Andrews is one of the nation’s leading beer and Red Bull distributors serving over 10,000 retail customers with a portfolio of more than 700 brands from 42 brewing partners. The Andrews team is comprised of 1,600 team members that are passionate about brand building.
Mike has served as president of Andrews since 2010 and has served on MillerCoors and Heineken’s national distributor councils. Prior to joining Andrews, Mike spent 16 years in high-tech sales and marketing leadership roles. Mike is an active board member of the Wholesale Beer Distributors of Texas as well as the National Beer Wholesalers Association. Mike serves on the Highland Park United Methodist Church Pastor Parish Relations Committee and on the advisory board of the S.M. Wright Foundation. Mike also serves on the Baylor Scott and White Hospital Advisory Board. Mike earned an MBA from the Cox School of Business at SMU and a Management Degree from Boston College. He and his wife Natalie are the loving parents of two daughters.






Executive Vice President/GM North Texas
Mike Barnes Read More >>
With over 25 years of experience in the beer industry, Mike currently serves as the General Manager for North Texas.  Mike started his career with Miller Brands in Denver and has held several positions at Andrews since relocating to Dallas...



Mike BarnesExecutive Vice President/GM North Texas

With over 25 years of experience in the beer industry, Mike currently serves as the General Manager for North Texas.  Mike started his career with Miller Brands in Denver and has held several positions at Andrews since relocating to Dallas in 1994. 
Mike holds an engineering degree from Central Missouri State University, where he was the team captain of the football team and also played rugby. Mike is involved with the National Charity League and serves on two National Distribution Advisory Councils.  He and his wife Darla have two children.






Chief Financial Officer - Business Operations
Roy Foster Read More >>
In leading Andrews financial business operations Roy is responsible for the internal Andrews strategic and tactical financial plans including reporting, budgeting, business planning, business and service unit support...



Roy FosterChief Financial Officer - Business Operations

In leading Andrews financial business operations Roy is responsible for the internal Andrews strategic and tactical financial plans including financial reporting, budgeting and business planning, business unit and service unit support and improving the operational profits of Andrews. Roy is a graduate of the University of North Texas with a Bachelors of Business Administration in Finance and a Masters of Business Administration-with Honors from SMU’s Cox School of Business. 






Vice President of Human Resources
David Garza Read More >>
David is a senior HR executive with over 24 years of HR and leadership experience. His capabilities in talent management and development align with our goal of developing our team into the nation’s leading beer and Red Bull brand builders.  



David GarzaVice President of Human Resources

David is a senior HR executive with over 24 years of HR and leadership experience. Before coming to Andrews, David led his own Human Resources consulting company, Compass Human Capital Advisors. During that time, he assumed the VP of Human Resources executive responsibilities at companies including Insight Equity and Reddy Ice. David previously held the VP of Human Resources position for Mission Foods, where he provided HR support for the company’s two divisions and 6,000 employees. He has also worked at Telvista Incorporated, the Regus Group, and in several other industries. His capabilities in talent management and development align with our goal of developing our team into the nations leading brand builders.
David grew up in Carrollton and graduated from the United States Military Academy at West Point, where he received a BS in Engineering with a focus of study in Organizational Behavior and Leadership. He served in the US Army for 6 and 1/2 years, including the Desert Storm Operation. His bravery in this operation was awarded with a Bronze Star and the Army Commendation Medal with “V” device for valor and heroism under enemy fire. After serving our country, David graduated from the University of Texas Austin’s McCombs School of Business with an MBA in Management. 






Vice President of Brand Building
David Holt Read More >>
David has been in the beer business since 1992. His past positions have spanned virtually every segment of Andrews’ business, including delivery, merchandising, special events, account management, district sales management...



David HoltVice President of Brand Building

David has been in the beer business since 1992. His past positions have spanned virtually every segment of Andrews’ business, including delivery, merchandising, special events, account management, district sales management, chain management and brand management.
David leads the Andrews brand management team, a group dedicated to the responsibility of building the Andrews portfolio of brands today and into the future. David is a graduate of Texas Christian University and has three children with his wife, Kristin.






Vice President of Marketing Services
Katy Wittig Read More >>
As Vice President of Marketing Services, Katy is responsible for supporting the sales team through business planning that drives brand building activities from our suppliers, brand management team and sales force. This team also oversees...



Katy WittigVice President of Marketing Services

As Vice President of Marketing Services, Katy is responsible for supporting the sales team through business planning that drives brand building activities from our suppliers, brand management team and sales force. This team also oversees the activation of supplier and internal programs through point of sale management and production. Katy leads the efforts of our creative team for both external program creation for our retailers and internal employee initiatives. Additionally, Katy supports Andrews’ overall communications strategy, focusing on employee engagement and effective external communication tactics.
Katy oversees our Distributing Cheer platform, the Andrews community involvement program which supports one of four Andrews strategic pillars, across all four areas of operation – Corpus Christi, Allen, Fort Worth and Dallas. She also helps support the activation of supplier involvement in local brand building events.
Katy is a graduate of Texas Tech University with a bachelors in marketing, and holds a graduate marketing and management certificate from Southern Methodist University. Katy is married and has two children.






Chief Financial Officer
